            "name": "wysiwyg_field",
            "type": "repeater",
            "instructions": "Each individual <em>WYSIWYG<\/em> field has an optional headline <em>(as an H3)<\/em>, and allows for different Bootstrap-based column layouts.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>Usage:<\/strong> In order to have two side-by-side WYSIWYG boxes, for example, create two WYSIWYG columns and select 'Two Column' for both layouts.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>Layout:<\/strong><br>\r\nFull-width: small-12 medium-12 large-12<br>\r\nTwo Column: small-12 medium-6 large-6<br>\r\nThree Column: small-12 medium-6 large-4<br>\r\nFour Column: small-12 medium-6 large-3<br>\r\nTwo-Thirds Area (Nine-Column): small-12 medium-8 large-9<br>\r\nOne-Third Area (Three Column): small-12 medium-4 large-3<br>",
